{"award_age":53.0,"bio_image":"full\/0714ae8dcc1a89e340d3eaf7f4def7f5db54f670.jpg","category":"Peace","country":"South Africa","date_of_birth":"1931-10-07T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/0\/0f\/Desmond_Tutu_2013-10-23_001.jpg\/220px-Desmond_Tutu_2013-10-23_001.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Desmond_Tutu","mini_bio":"<p><b>Desmond Mpilo Tutu<\/b> (born 7 October 1931) is a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/South_Africa\" title=\"South Africa\">South African<\/a> social rights activist and retired <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Anglicanism\" title=\"Anglicanism\">Anglican<\/a> bishop who rose to worldwide fame during the 1980s as an opponent of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Apartheid\" title=\"Apartheid\">apartheid<\/a>.<\/p><p>He was the first black <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Archbishop_of_Cape_Town\" title=\"Archbishop of Cape Town\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Archbishop of Cape Town<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bishop\" title=\"Bishop\">bishop<\/a> of the Church of the Province of Southern Africa (now the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Anglican_Church_of_Southern_Africa\" title=\"Anglican Church of Southern Africa\">Anglican Church of Southern Africa<\/a>).<\/p><p>Tutu's admirers see him as a man who since the demise of apartheid has been active in the defence of human rights and uses his high profile to campaign for the oppressed. He has campaigned to fight <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/HIV\/AIDS\" title=\"HIV\/AIDS\">HIV\/AIDS<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Tuberculosis\" title=\"Tuberculosis\">tuberculosis<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Poverty\" title=\"Poverty\">poverty<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Racism\" title=\"Racism\">racism<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sexism\" title=\"Sexism\">sexism<\/a>, the imprisonment of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chelsea_Manning\" title=\"Chelsea Manning\">Chelsea Manning<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Homophobia\" title=\"Homophobia\">homophobia<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Transphobia\" title=\"Transphobia\">transphobia<\/a>. He received the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Peace Prize\">Nobel Peace Prize<\/a> in 1984; the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Albert_Schweitzer_Prize_for_Humanitarianism\" title=\"Albert Schweitzer Prize for Humanitarianism\">Albert Schweitzer Prize for Humanitarianism<\/a> in 1986; the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pacem_in_Terris_Award\" title=\"Pacem in Terris Award\">Pacem in Terris Award<\/a> in 1987; the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sydney_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Sydney Peace Prize\">Sydney Peace Prize<\/a> in 1999; the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Gandhi_Peace_Prize\" title=\"Gandhi Peace Prize\">Gandhi Peace Prize<\/a> in 2007;<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Desmond_Tutu#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> and the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Presidential_Medal_of_Freedom\" title=\"Presidential Medal of Freedom\">Presidential Medal of Freedom<\/a> in 2009. He has also compiled several books of his speeches and sayings.<\/p>","name":"Desmond Tutu","place_of_birth":"Klerksdorp ,  Western Transvaal , South Africa","place_of_death":null,"text":"Desmond Tutu , Peace, 1984","year":1984.0}